law.text:
Nothing in KRS 200.650 to 200.676 shall be construed to permit the following:
The reduction of local, state, or federal medical or other assistance available for infants and toddlers with disabilities and their families;
The alteration of eligibility under Title V of the Federal Social Security Act relating to maternal and child health;
The alteration of eligibility under Title XIX of the Federal Social Security Act relating to Medicaid for infants and toddlers with disabilities; or
The reduction of early intervention services provided by any state department or agency.
